.TH YAML_DEPTH 3 "2026-06-30" "libyaml 0.1.0" "libyaml library"
.SH NAME
yaml_depth, yaml_parser_state \- context status queries
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <yaml.h>
.PP
.BI "int yaml_depth(yaml_ctx_t *" ctx ");"
.BI "const char *yaml_parser_state(yaml_ctx_t *" ctx ");"
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.BR yaml_depth ()
returns the current nesting depth of the context. For a parser context,
this is the indentation depth; for a serializer context, this is the
serialization depth. A return value of 0 indicates top level.
Returns \-1 if
.I ctx
is NULL.
.PP
.BR yaml_parser_state ()
returns a human-readable string describing the current parser state.
Possible values include \(lqIDLE\(rq, \(lqSTREAM\(rq, \(lqDOCUMENT\(rq, and \(lqDONE\(rq.
Returns NULL if
.I ctx
is NULL or the context role is not
.BR YAML_ROLE_PARSER .
.SH RETURN VALUE
.BR yaml_depth ()
returns the current nesting depth as a non-negative integer,
or \-1 if
.I ctx
is NULL.
.PP
.BR yaml_parser_state ()
returns a pointer to a static string, or NULL if the context is NULL
or not a parser.
.SH THREAD SAFETY
Not thread-safe. Use from a single thread at a time.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR yaml_create (3),
.BR yaml_next_event (3),
.BR yaml_has_pending_events (3)
